Articles.Content:
Floor 2625: A giant bank of monitors showing multiple floors, places you have been. Seems that maybe more people are keeping tabs on your journey.

Oh hey look, I edited my post because I didn't notice it was a new page when I first did it.

Edited February 12, 2022 by ColdJ

Floor 2626: A song for a new page:

The days have come
A good positive outcome
Of our fiddling with floors
Mischievous robots and great colors
 

Oh, 53 times 2 is 106
That's where we are!
We welcome page 106
And I resigned from writing songs!

Edited February 12, 2022 by Kerbal Productions

Floor 2627: The place is nothing but stairs. Lots of stairs. After three hours of searching, trying and failing, you manage to get to next floor.

Edited February 12, 2022 by Nazalassa

After reading a strange sign showing "CATS ON KEYBOARD", you go to next floor.

Edited February 13, 2022 by Nazalassa

Floor 2630: Thay are playing Simon and Garfunkels "The Sound of Cylons"

The door to the next floor opens, by your command.
Floor 2631: The Lounge. You have finally arrived.
Floor 2632: Only the next grade of the Lounge can come in. You run away in panic.
Floor 2633: Galaxies Unbound's hall of planets. Every 100+ celestial bodies in a floor! StarCrusher and his team will love this!
Fllor 2634: Galaxies got bound.
Fllor 2635: you started to name floors "Fllors", how creative, right?
Floor 2636: That got old very quickly. Here they are playing Sins of a Solar Empire. You play a game and finally finish it a week later.
Floor 237: It's since sins.
Floor 2(6)38: Dynasty of time and space
Floor 2639: A Sushi train.
Floor 2640: Still smells fishy.
Floor 2641: the last great american dynasty
Floor 2642: The Ottoman Empire. Recliners half price.

Floow 2642: Damage Control Room. Anyone remember when all of the floors below a number I forget collapsed? A large screen on the wall says "Building Reconstruction Complete". Good to know. You head into the elevator and to to the next floor.
Floor 2644: The 3x+1 problem video of Veritasium playing on a 4k TV

Floor 2645: A wall sized 8k monitor dominates the room the fidelity is amazing, it is showing you outer space above the planet with the horizon a curve in the distance. It seems so real that you reach out to touch it.

Oh wait, it's just a window. You head on up.

Fllor 2646.

Something liquid is dropping from the floor 2647.
Floor 2647: A little child is crying because they dropped their icecream and it is dripping down the stairs.
Door 2648: What is this, a door or a floor?
Floor 2649. A doorway to Norway.
